The paper introduces a new method for analyzing high-dimensional neural spiking data, which involves a sequential model based on a variational auto-encoder and a dynamical systems hypothesis. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), systems and control (cs.SD), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
